---
import Site from '../layouts/Site.astro';
---

<Site
  title="About"
  description="The story behind The Owl's Nest — a small short-term rental in Redmond, Oregon."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>
        The Owl's Nest is a single-family home in central Redmond, Oregon, hosted
        and maintained directly by its owner. We built it for the kind of trip
        that doesn't fit a glossy brochure — early starts at Smith Rock, slow
        afternoons in town, and the high-desert sky after dinner.
      </p>

      <h2>What you can expect</h2>
      <p>
        A clean, considered home with full amenities: kitchen, laundry, fast wifi,
        comfortable beds, and a back patio that's a near-perfect spot for golden
        hour. Up to four guests. No surprise fees. Direct text-message support if
        something needs attention.
      </p>

      <h2>Why we host directly</h2>
      <p>
        Booking through us means no platform service fees and a faster, more
        personal answer when you have questions. We use the same channel managers
        and quality controls a larger operation would, but with a single point of
        contact: the owner.
      </p>

      <h2>How to reach us</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way is the booking flow on the <a href="/book">Book</a> page —
        we'll respond personally to inquiries within a few hours during normal
        waking hours.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Site>
